ries.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In 2022, Philly Jobs With Justice is launching a campaign to build worker power and fight for new workplace health and safety legislation in Philadelphia. The Mobilization Organizer will play a critical role in this campaign by recruiting and developing a cohort of activists, working in coalition with allied organizations, bottomlining logistics on actions and events, and executing a communications strategy. The Organizer will work closely with the Director and the Workplace Justice Organizer.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This position will include both remote and in-person activity as conditions allow. Candidates must be located in the greater Philadelphia area with the ability to travel throughout the city. Salary range for this position is $48,000-$52,000 with generous paid time off and medical and dental benefits.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Primary Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>Working with the Director to develop and execute a plan to recruit a cohort of individual activists using a variety of tactics and strategies;</li><li>Working with the director to coordinate a coalition of partner organizations;</li><li>Planning and executing logistics on actions and events including rallies, press conferences, legislative hearings, and digital actions;</li><li>Mobilizing individual activists and members of partner organizations for actions and events;</li><li>Developing a comprehensive communications strategy including social media and press outreach;</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Qualifications:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>Minimum 2 years experience with campaign organizing, familiarity with worker organizing preferred;</li><li>Demonstrated experience with communications strategies including social media and pre